# ShellCheck configuration for the Prilive Go TDD Pack.
#
# Policy: shellcheck -S warning is BLOCKING in CI as of v2.0.1
# (.github/workflows/ci.yml — see the `lint` job). All scripts must
# pass at warning level. Info-level findings are advisory.
#
# No global disables. Each script that needs an exception uses an
# inline `# shellcheck disable=SCXXXX` directive with a comment
# explaining why. As of v2.0.1 there is exactly one such exception:
#
#   runner/codex-round1.sh:SC2038 — find|xargs pipeline for Codex
#   session ID. Whole pipeline is planned for replacement in task
#   #103 (v2.1.0 Codex modernization), so don't fix in isolation.
#
# To run locally:
#   shellcheck -S warning hooks/*.sh runner/*.sh test/*.sh \
#     scripts/github-setup/*.sh scripts/github-setup/lib/*.sh
#
# To check what the next stricter level would flag (info):
#   shellcheck -S info ...
